This paper deals with automated deduction and theorem proving, which are core topics in logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a novel form of clause abstraction, which is a technique used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the hierarchic superposition calculus, which is a data structure used in computer science for efficient storage and retrieval of information (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses completeness results, which are a fundamental concept in software engineering and verification (cs.SE).
